title: Identity Python PySAML2 security bypass
description: Identity Python PySAML2 could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by not validating the SAML document against an XML schema. By persuading a victim to open a specially-crafted XML document, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to process invalid SAML XML documents.

title: Identity Python PySAML2 security bypass
description: Identity Python PySAML2 could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by not ensure that a signed SAML document is correctly signed by the xmlsec1 binary. By persuading a victim to open a specially-crafted XML document, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to process invalid SAML XML documents.

title: Python PyCArg_repr function buffer overflow
description: Python is vulnerable to a buffer overflow, caused by improper bounds checking by the PyCArg_repr function in _ctypes/callproc.c. By sending specially-crafted arguments to c_double.from_param, a remote attacker could overflow a buffer and execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Python Flask-Security-Too package cross-site request forgery
description: Python Flask-Security-Too package is vulnerable to cross-site request forgery, caused by improper validation of user-supplied input by the /login and /change endpoints. By persuading an authenticated user to visit a malicious Web site, a remote attacker could send a malformed HTTP request to obtain the authentication token information. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to perform cross-site scripting attacks, Web cache poisoning, and other malicious activities.

title: Crossbar.io Autobahn|Python header injection
description: Crossbar.io Autobahn|Python is vulnerable to HTTP header injection, caused by improper validation of input. By persuading a victim to visit a specially-crafted Web page, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to inject arbitrary HTTP headers, which will allow the attacker to conduct various attacks against the vulnerable system, including cross-site scripting, cache poisoning or session hijacking.

title: python-apt denial of service
description: python-apt is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by various memory and file descriptor leaks in apt-python files python/arfile.cc, python/tag.cc, python/tarfile.cc. By persuading a victim to open a specially crafted file, a local attacker could exploit this vulnerability to consume all available resources.

title: OpenIDC Python OpenID Connect security bypass
description: OpenIDC Python OpenID Connect could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by multiple cryptographic issues. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to perform replay attack and cipher downgrade.

title: Python LXML cross-site scripting
description: Python LXML is vulnerable to cross-site scripting, caused by improper validation of user-supplied input by the clean module. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability using a specially-crafted URL to execute script in a victim's Web browser within the security context of the hosting Web site, once the URL is clicked. An attacker could use this vulnerability to steal the victim's cookie-based authentication credentials.

title: python-cryptography information disclosure
description: python-cryptography could allow a remote attacker to obtain sensitive information, caused by a Bleichenbacher timing attack. By sending a specially-crafted request using the RSA decryption API, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to obtain parts of the cipher text encrypted with RSA, and use this information to launch further attacks against the affected system.

title: Apple macOS Big Sur security bypass
description: Apple macOS Big Sur could allow a local attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by multiple issues in the python or Ruby component. By using a specially-crafted application, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to modify the file system.

title: Python-RSA information disclosure
description: Python-RSA could allow a remote attacker to obtain sensitive information, caused by a Bleichenbacher timing attack. By sending a specially-crafted request using the RSA decryption API, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to obtain parts of the cipher text encrypted with RSA, and use this information to launch further attacks against the affected system.

title: lookatme (python/pypi package) command execution
description: lookatme (python/pypi package) could allow a remote authenticated attacker to execute arbitrary commands on the system, caused by an issue when automatically loading the built-in terminal and file_loader extensions. By persuading a victim to render a specially-crafted markdown, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary shell commands on the system.

title: Synopsys hub-rest-api-python (aka blackduck on PyPI) man-in-the-middle attack
description: Synopsys hub-rest-api-python (aka blackduck on PyPI) is vulnerable to a man-in-the-middle attack, caused by improper validation of SSL certificates in certain cases. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to launch a man-in-the-middle attack and gain access to the communication channel between endpoints to obtain sensitive information or further compromise the system.

title: ReQuest Serious Play F3 Media Server information disclosure
description: ReQuest Serious Play F3 Media Server could allow a remote attacker to obtain sensitive information, caused by a debug log disclosure vulnerability. By visiting the message_log page, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to obtain the webserver's Python debug log file containing other sensitive information.
platform: ReQuest Serious Play F3 Media Server 7.0.3

title: Microsoft Visual Studio Code code execution
description: Microsoft Visual Studio Code could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by an error when the Python extension loads a Jupyter notebook file. By persuading a victim to open specially-crafted content, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system with privileges of the victim.

title: Python multibytecodec_support.py unspecified
description: An unspecified error with CJK codec tests call eval() on content retrieved throug HTTP in multibytecodec_support.py in Python has an unknown impact and attack vector.

title: Python http.client CRLF injection
description: Python is vulnerable to CRLF injection, caused by improper validation of user-supplied input in http.client. By inserting CR and LF control characters in the first argument of HTTPConnection.request, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to conduct various attacks against the vulnerable system, including cross-site scripting, cache poisoning or session hijacking.

title: Python TUF (The Update Framework) reference implementation security bypass
description: Python TUF (The Update Framework) could allow a <remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by an issue when incorrectly trusting a previously downloaded root metadata file which failed verification at download time. By using multiple new versions of root metadata, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to control the trust chain for future updates.

title: Python Py denial of service
description: Python Py is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by a regular expression in the svnwc.py component. By supplying malicious input to the blame functionality, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause a compute-time denial of service.

title: Django security bypass
description: Django could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by improper permissions in intermediate-level directories of the file system cache. By using Python 3.7+, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to bypass access restrictions.

title: Scalyr Agent man-in-the-middle
description: Scalyr Agent is vulnerable to a man-in-the-middle attack, caused by missing SSL certificate validation when the native Python code is used but lacks a comparison of the hostname to commonName and subjectAltName. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to launch a man-in-the-middle attack and gain access to the communication channel between endpoints to obtain sensitive information or further compromise the system.

title: ROS actionlib code execution
description: ROS actionlib could allow a local or remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by an unsafe parsing of YAML values. By using a specially-crafted payload, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code in Python on the system.

title: openapi-python-client code execution
description: openapi-python-client could allow a remote authenticated attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by an error when a specially crafted OpenAPI Document is used to generate arbitrary Python code. By sending a specially crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: openapi-python-client directory traversal
description: openapi-python-client could allow a remote authenticated attacker to traverse directories on the system. By using a specially crafted OpenAPI document, an attacker could send a specially-crafted URL request containing "dot dot" sequences (/../) to generate arbitrary files on the system.

title: SABnzbd command execution
description: SABnzbd could allow a remote authenticated attacker to execute arbitrary commands on the system, caused by a command injection flaw in the web configuration interface. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary Python commands on the underlying operating system.

title: Python tarfile.py denial of service
description: Python is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by a flaw in the tarfile module in Lib/tarfile.py. By persuading a victim to open a specially-craft a TAR archive, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause the application to enter into an infinite loop.

title: Dogtag PKI man-in-the-middle
description: Dogtag PKI is vulnerable to a man-in-the-middle attack, caused by not enabling python-requests certificate validation in the pki.client.PKIConnection class. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to launch a man-in-the-middle attack and gain access to the communication channel between endpoints to obtain sensitive information or further compromise the system.

title: Python sys.path code execution
description: Python could allow a local attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by an issue with sys.path restrictions specified in a python38._pth file are ignored. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Beaker library for Python code execution
description: Beaker library for Python could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by an unsafe deserialization in the cache database. By sending specially-crafted input, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Python ipaddress.py denial of service
description: Python is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by improper computing hash values in the IPv4Interface and IPv6Interface classes in Lib/ipaddress.py. By sending a specially-crafted request, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause a denial of service condition.

title: Python-RSA denial of service
description: Python-RSA is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by a flaw during the decryption of ciphertext. By sending a specially-crafted request, a local attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause a denial of service condition.

title: Apple macOS Catalina code execution
description: Apple macOS Catalina could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by a memory corruption in the Python component. By persuading a victim to visit a specially-crafted Web site, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Contentful cross-site scripting
description: Contentful for Python is vulnerable to cross-site scripting, caused by improper validation of user-supplied input by the the-example-app.py. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability using the api parameter in a specially-crafted URL to execute script in a victim's Web browser within the security context of the hosting Web site, once the URL is clicked. An attacker could use this vulnerability to steal the victim's cookie-based authentication credentials.

title: Python jw.util package code execution
description: Python jw.util package could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by a flaw in the configuration-loading functionality. By sending a specially crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Open edX Ironwood code execution
description: Open edX Ironwood could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by the failure to use CodeJail. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to go to the Create New course>New section>New subsection>New unit>Add new component>Problem button>Advanced tab>Custom Python evaluated code screen, edit the problem and execute Python code on the system.

title: Autoswitch Python Virtualenv code execution
description: Autoswitch Python Virtualenv could allow a remote authenticated attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by improper input validation. By using a specially-crafted .venv file, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.
platform: Autoswitch Python Virtualenv Autoswitch Python Virtualenv 1.15.2

title: Microsoft Visual Studio Code code execution
description: Microsoft Visual Studio Code could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by a flaw in the Python extension. By persuading a victim to open a specially-crafted file, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Plex Media Server code execution
description: Plex Media Server could allow a remote authenticated attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by a deserialization of untrusted data vulnerability. By sending a specially crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary Python code on the system.

title: Plex Media Server code execution
description: Plex Media Server could allow a local attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by improper input validation. By sending a specially crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary Python code with SYSTEM privileges.

title: python-markdown2 cross-site scripting
description: python-markdown2 is vulnerable to cross-site scripting, caused by improper validation of user-supplied input. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability using element names in a specially-crafted URL to execute script in a victim's Web browser within the security context of the hosting Web site, once the URL is clicked. An attacker could use this vulnerability to steal the victim's cookie-based authentication credentials.

title: svglib external entity injection
description: svglib package for Python could allow a remote attacker to obtain sensitive information, caused by improper handling of XML external entity (XXE) in binary/BinaryMapIndexReader.java. By sending a specially-crafted HTTP request, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to obtain sensitive information or cause a denial of service.

title: Python safety package code execution
description: Python safety package could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by a flaw in the Safety Command-Line Tool. By sending a specially crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Microsoft VSCode Python Extension code execution
description: Microsoft VSCode could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by a flaw in the Python Extension. By persuading a victim to clone a specially-crafted repository, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: PyYAML code execution
description: PyYAML could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by an error when processing untrusted YAML files through the full_load method or with the FullLoader loader. By abusing the python/object/new constructor, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Zyxel CloudCNM SecuManager security bypass
description: Zyxel CloudCNM SecuManager could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by the use of q6xV4aW8bQ4cfD-b password for the axiros account. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to download and upload python code, templates, webpages and ZEXPs.

title: Druva inSync Mac OS Client code execution
description: Druva inSync Mac OS Client could allow a local authenticated attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by improper neutralization of directives in dynamically evaluated code. By sending specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary Python expressions with root privileges.

title: Python denial of service
description: Python is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by a flaw in the urllib.request.AbstractBasicAuthHandler. By sending a specially crafted request, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause a Regular Expression Denial of Service (ReDoS).

title: TensorFlow tf.float16 value denial of service
description: Tensorflow is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by a flaw when converting a string (from Python) to a tf.float16 value. By sending a specially-crafted string, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause a segmentation fault.

title: Python interface to the apt package manager security bypass
description: Python interface to the apt package manager could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to install packages from untrusted repositories.

title: Python interface to the apt package manager man-in-the-middle
description: Python interface to the apt package manager is vulnerable to a man-in-the-middle attack, caused by the continued use of MD5 hashes to validate certain downloaded packages. By using man-in-the-middle techniques, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to install altered packages.

title: Python code execution
description: Python could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by an insecure dependency load upon launch on Windows 7. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Mozilla Firefox code execution
description: Mozilla Firefox could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by an error when Python was installed on Windows. By persuading a victim to visit a specially-crafted Web site, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to inadvertently execute Python files upon opening a download.

title: Pillow TIFF decoding buffer overflow
description: Python Pillow is vulnerable to an integer overflow, caused by improper calculation of memory block reallocation by libImaging/TiffDecode.c. By persuading a victim to open a specially-crafted TIFF image, a remote attacker could overflow a buffer and cause the application to crash.

title: Python Pillow PCX buffer overflow
description: Python Pillow is vulnerable to a buffer overflow, caused by improper bounds checking by libImaging/PcxDecode.c. By persuading a victim to open a specially-crafted PCX file, a remote attacker could overflow a buffer and execute arbitrary code on the system or cause the application to crash.

title: Python Pillow SGI buffer overflow
description: Python Pillow is vulnerable to a buffer overflow, caused by improper bounds checking by libImaging/SgiRleDecode.c. By persuading a victim to open a specially-crafted SGI file, a remote attacker could overflow a buffer and execute arbitrary code on the system or cause the application to crash.

title: Python Pillow FLI buffer overflow
description: Python Pillow is vulnerable to a buffer overflow, caused by improper bounds checking by libImaging/FliDecode.c. By persuading a victim to open a specially-crafted FLI file, a remote attacker could overflow a buffer and execute arbitrary code on the system or cause the application to crash.

title: Python Pillow package denial of service
description: Python Pillow package is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by an OverflowError or MemoryError in FpxImagePlugin.py. By persuading a victim to open a specially-crafted file, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause a denial of service condition.

title: python-ecdsa DER encoding denial of service
description: python-ecdsa is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by the failure to verify DER encoding in signatures. By using specially-crafted DER signatures, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause a denial of service.

title: python-markdown2 cross-site scripting
description: python-markdown2 is vulnerable to cross-site scripting, caused by improper validation of user-supplied input. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute script in a victim's Web browser within the security context of the hosting Web site. An attacker could use this vulnerability to steal the victim's cookie-based authentication credentials.

title: Python urllib2 header injection
description: Python is vulnerable to HTTP header injection, caused by improper validation of input in the urllib2. By sending a specially-crafted request, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to inject arbitrary HTTP headers, which will allow the attacker to conduct various attacks against the vulnerable system, including cross-site scripting, cache poisoning or session hijacking.

title: python-ecdsa denial of service
description: python-ecdsa is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by an error-handling flaw. By using malformed DER signatures, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause the application to crash.

title: Python DocXMLRPCServer.py cross-site scripting
description: Python is vulnerable to cross-site scripting, caused by improper validation of user-supplied input by the python/Lib/DocXMLRPCServer.py. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability using the server_title field to inject malicious script into a Web page which would be executed in a victim's Web browser within the security context of the hosting Web site, once the URL is clicked. An attacker could use this vulnerability to steal the victim's cookie-based authentication credentials.

title: pam-python privilege escalation
description: pam-python could allow a local authenticated attacker to gain elevated privileges on the system, caused by a flaw in the default environment variable handling of Python. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to escalate privileges in certain PAM setups.

title: Elastic APM agent for Python information disclosure
description: Elastic APM agent for Python could allow a remote attacker to obtain sensitive information, caused by a variable name clash flaw. By using a specially-crafted proxy header, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to obtain sensitive information.

title: python-engineio webSocket security bypass
description: python-engineio could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by a cross-site webSocket hijacking (CSWSH) vulnerability. By persuading a victim to visit a specially-crafted Web site, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to initiate webSocket connections to a server.

title: Python novajoin plugin privilege escalation
description: Python novajoin plugin could allow a remote authenticated attacker to gain elevated privileges on the system, caused by improper access control in the novajoin API. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to generate FreeIPA tokens.

title: Python urllib.parse.urlsplit and urllib.parse.urlparse components information disclosure
description: Python urllib.parse.urlsplit and urllib.parse.urlparse components could allow a remote attacker to obtain sensitive information, caused by improper unicode encoding handling. By using a specially-crafted URL, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to obtain sensitive information.

title: Python Parso code execution
description: Python Parso could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by a deserialization flaw. By persuading a victim to open a specially-crafted cache grammar file, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Cisco NX-OS Software privilege escalation
description: Cisco NX-OS Software could allow a local authenticated attacker to gain elevated privileges on the system, caused by improper input validation by the parameters passed to Python functions in the scripting sandbox. By sending a specially-crafted request, an authenticated attacker could exploit this vulnerability to escape the scripting sandbox and execute arbitrary commands with elevated privileges.

title: pypa pip package for python directory traversal
description: pypa pip package for python could allow a remote attacker to traverse directories on the system, caused by a flaw when installing package via a specified URL. An attacker could use a specially-crafted Content-Disposition header with filename containing "dot dot" sequences (/../) to overwrite arbitrary files on the system.

title: Python ast.c denial of service
description: Python is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by a handle_keywordonly_args out-of-bounds read in Python/ast.c. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to crash the interpreter process.

title: Python ast.c denial of service
description: Python is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by an ast_for_arguments out-of-bounds read in Python/ast.c. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to crash the interpreter process.

title: Python urllib3 request parameter CRLF injection
description: Python urllib3 is vulnerable to CRLF injection, caused by improper validation of user-supplied input by the request parameter. By sending a specially-crafted HTTP response containing CRLF character sequences, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to conduct various attacks against the vulnerable system, including cross-site scripting, cache poisoning or session hijacking.

title: Python urllib2 header injection
description: Python is vulnerable to HTTP header injection, caused by improper validation of input in the urllib2. By sending a specially-crafted request, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to inject arbitrary HTTP headers, which will allow the attacker to conduct various attacks against the vulnerable system, including cross-site scripting, cache poisoning or session hijacking.

title: Python denial of service
description: Python is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by a flaw in the Lib/zipfile.py. By using a ZIP bomb, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause a denial of dervice.

title: Python urllib.parse.urlsplit and urllib.parse.urlparse components information disclosure
description: Python urllib.parse.urlsplit and urllib.parse.urlparse components could allow a remote attacker to obtain sensitive information, caused by improper unicode encoding handling in NFKC normalization. By using a specially-crafted URL, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to obtain sensitive information.

title: Digi TransPort LR54 command execution
description: Digi TransPort LR54 could allow a remote authenticated attacker to execute arbitrary commands on the system, caused by the improper handling of command line arguments when executing python scripts by the CLI. By sending a specially crafted argument, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary commands on the system with root privileges.

title: Facebook Thrift Python denial of service
description: Facebook Thrift is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by improper handling of messages in the Python Facebook Thrift servers. By sending a specially-crafted message, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause the application to stop responding.

title: RDFLib python-rdflib-tools package code execution
description: RDFLib python-rdflib-tools package could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by a code injection flaw in the CLI tools. By sending a specially-crafted arguments, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Python urllib security bypass
description: Python could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by improper input validation by the urllib. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to bypass the blacklist file: URIs protection mechanisms.

title: Python urllib and urllib2 header injection
description: Python is vulnerable to HTTP header injection, caused by improper validation of input in urllib and urllib2. By persuading a victim to visit a specially-crafted Web page, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to inject arbitrary HTTP headers, which will allow the attacker to conduct various attacks against the vulnerable system, including cross-site scripting, cache poisoning or session hijacking.

title: python-libnmap denial of service
description: python-libnmap is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by XML Injection in XML Parsing. By sending a specially crafted XML payload, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause the application to crash.

title: python-gnupg gnupg.GPG.encrypt() and gnupg.GPG.decrypt() methods security bypass
description: python-gnupg could provide weaker than expected security, caused by improper input validation in the gnupg.GPG.encrypt() and gnupg.GPG.decrypt() methods. By supplying a specially-crafted passphrase, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to control or modify the ciphertext/plaintext being decrypted or encrypted.

title: NumPy Pickle module code execution
description: NumPy could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by the unsafe use of the pickle Python module. By using a specially-crafted serialized object, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Oracle MySQL Connectors Connector/Python unspecified
description: An unspecified vulnerability in Oracle MySQL related to the Connectors Connector/Python component could allow an unauthenticated attacker to cause high confidentiality impact, high integrity impact, and no availability impact.

title: Splunk Splunk-SDK-Python man-in-the-middle
description: Splunk Splunk-SDK-Python is vulnerable to a man-in-the-middle attack, caused by improper validation of TLS server certificates. By sending a specially crafted certificate, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to conduct man-in-the-middle attacks.

title: Sqla_yaml_fixtures sqla_yaml_fixtures.load code execution
description: Sqla_yaml_fixtures could allow a local attacker to execute arbitrary python code on the system, caused by improper input validation by the fixture_text argument in sqla_yaml_fixtures.load. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary python code on the system.

title: Danijar Hafner definitions package for Python parser.py. command execution
description: Danijar Hafner definitions package for Python could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary commands on the system, caused by a flaw in the load() method in definitions/parser.py. By using a specially-crafted file, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary commands on the system.
platform: Python Danijar Hafner definitions package for Python

title: ymlref api.load method command execution
description: ymlref could allow a local attacker to execute arbitrary commands on the system, caused by a flaw in the api.load method in ymlref.api.py. By sending specially-crafted arguments, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary Python commands on the system.

title: JPCERTCC LogonTracer code execution
description: JPCERTCC LogonTracer could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to inject and execute arbitrary Python code on the system.

title: Python cookiejar.py information disclosure
description: Python could allow a remote attacker to obtain sensitive information, caused by the failure to correctly validate the domain by http.cookiejar.DefaultPolicy.domain_return_ok in Lib/http/cookiejar.py. By using a server with a hostname that has another valid hostname as a suffix, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to obtain leaked existing cookies.

title: The Requests package for Python information disclosure
description: The Requests package for Python could allow a remote attacker to obtain sensitive information, caused by sending information in an insecure manner. By sniffing the network, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to obtain sensitive information.

title: Imperva SecureSphere command execution
description: Imperva SecureSphere could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary commands on the system, caused by improper input validation in the Python CGI scripts in PWS. By sending a specially-crafted command, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary OS commands on the system.

title: Python elementtree C accelerator denial of service
description: Python is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by a flaw in the elementtree C accelerator. By using a specially-crafted XML document, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause a resource exhaustion.

title: Python _pickle.c denial of service
description: Python is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by an integer overflow in the Modules/_pickle.c. By using a large LONG_BINPUT value, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to exhaust all available memory resources.

title: Intel Distribution for Python (IDP) privilege escalation
description: Intel Distribution for Python (IDP) could allow a local authenticated attacker to gain elevated privileges on the system, caused by an incorrect default install directory permission issue. By using a specially-crafted file, an authenticated attacker could exploit this vulnerability to gain elevated privileges.

title: Python shutil module command execution
description: Python could allow a local attacker to execute arbitrary commands on the system, caused by a flaw in the shutil module (make_archive function). By using a specially-crafted file, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary commands on the system.

title: glot-www os.system command execution
description: glot-www could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary commands on the system, caused by the supporting of os.system within a python files content JSON file. By sending specially-crafted command arguments, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary commands on the system.

title: PyCryptodome package for Python AESNI_encrypt and AESNI_decrypt functions denial of service
description: PyCryptodome package for Python is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by an integer overflow in the AESNI_encrypt and AESNI_decrypt functions in AESNI.c. By sending a specially-crafted data to data_len variable, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause Python to crash.

title: Python cryptography package finalize_with_tag API security bypass
description: Python cryptography package could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by the failure to enforce a minimum tag length in the finalize_with_tag API. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to bypass the MAC check.

title: Python email module security bypass
description: Python could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by an issue with email module incorrectly parsing email address containing multiple @ characters. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to bypass email filtering protection.

title: Intel Distribution for Python denial of service
description: Intel Distribution for Python is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by the improper validation of input in Bleach module. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to bypass URI sanitization and cause a denial of service.

title: Python pop3lib's apop() method denial of service
description: Python is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by catastrophic backtracking in the pop3lib's apop() method. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause the application to crash.

title: Python difflib.IS_LINE_JUNK method denial of service
description: Python is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by catastrophic backtracking in the difflib.IS_LINE_JUNK method. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause the application to crash.

title: Validators package for Python denial of service
description: Validators package for Python is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by an error when validators.domain is called. By sending a specially-crafted domain string, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause the application to enter into an infinite loop.

title: Oracle Sun Systems Solaris Python modules unspecified
description: An unspecified vulnerability in Oracle Sun Systems related to the Solaris Python modules component could allow an authenticated attacker to cause high confidentiality impact, high integrity impact, and no availability impact.

title: Python glob.html weak security
description: Python could provide weaker than expected security, caused by a flaw in the library/glob.html which could mislead information about whether sorting occurs. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to launch further attacks on the system.

title: marshmallow library for Python schema only option information disclosure
description: marshmallow library for Python could allow a remote attacker to obtain sensitive information, caused by a flaw in the implementation of schema only option. By sending a specially-crafted data, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to obtain sensitive information.

title: Python CPytho os.symlink() function buffer overflow
description: Python CPytho is vulnerable to a buffer overflow, caused by improper bounds checking by os.symlink() function. By using a python script that creates a symlink with an attacker controlled name or location, a local attacker could overflow a buffer and execute arbitrary code on the system with elevated privileges.

title: Python Bleach package URI value security bypass
description: Python Bleach package could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by improper validation of URI values. By using character entities in the URL values, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to bypass access restrictions.

title: New Relic Java, Python, and .NET agents command execution
description: New Relic Java, Python, and .NET agents could allow a remote attacker to execute SQL commands on the database, caused by running multiple statements separated by semicolons in a single query. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to return the results of the additional statements and execute an additional INSERT or UPDATE command on the database.

title: Duo Network Gateway python-saml security bypass
description: Duo Network Gateway (DNG) could allow a remote authenticated attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by an implementation flaw in a third-party library. By adding or modifying specially crafted XML data, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to modify digital signatures of user attribute data and impersonate a user or obtain potentially sensitive information.

title: OneLogin python-saml security bypass
description: OneLogin could allow a remote authenticated attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by an implementation flaw in the python-saml open-source library. By adding or modifying specially crafted XML data, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to modify digital signatures of user attribute data and impersonate a user or obtain potentially sensitive information.

title: Juniper AppFormix command execution
description: Juniper AppFormix could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary commands on the system, caused by an error in the application management platform. By accessing a Python debug console, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary commands on the system with root privileges.

title: Dell EMC Isilon OneFS privilege escalation
description: Dell EMC Isilon OneFS could allow a remote attacker to gain elevated privileges on the system, caused by a path traversal when reading the script file to run. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability using remote support scripts to execute arbitrary python code with root privileges.

title: Green Electronics RainMachine Mini-8 (2nd generation) code execution
description: Green Electronics RainMachine Mini-8 (2nd generation) could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by improper input validation by the Weather Service feature. By sending specially-crafted data to the 'Add new weather data source' upload function, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary Python code on the system.

title: markdown2 safe_mode feature cross-site scripting
description: markdown2 (aka python-markdown2) is vulnerable to cross-site scripting, caused by improper validation of user-supplied input by the safe_mode feature. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to inject malicious script into a Web page which would be executed in a victim's Web browser within the security context of the hosting Web site, once the page is viewed. An attacker could use this vulnerability to steal the victim's cookie-based authentication credentials.

title: New Relic Python agent High Security Mode information disclosure
description: New Relic Python agent could allow a remote attacker to obtain sensitive information, caused by an error when High Security Mode is enabled. By customizing message params with the tracing APIs, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to capture custom API parameters in High Security Mode.

title: New Relic Python agent SQL query parameters security bypass
description: New Relic Python agent could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by the failure to properly obfuscate SQL query parameters. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to send SQL query parameters with double quoted strings.

title: Electrum Python console security bypass
description: Electrum could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by a flaw in the Python console. By persuading a victim to paste a specially-crafted exploit code, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to steal Bitcoin.

title: Python package for Debian webbrowser.py security bypass
description: Python package for Debian could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by improper validation of strings before launching the program specified by the BROWSER environment variable in Lib/webbrowser.py. By using a specially-crafted URL, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to conduct argument injection attacks.

title: Cisco NX-OS System Software security bypass
description: Cisco NX-OS System Software could allow a local authenticated attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by a flaw in the Python scripting sandbox. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to scape the scripting sandbox and access Bash shell.

title: pysaml2 package for Python weak security
description: pysaml2 package for Python could provide weaker than expected security, caused by reusing the initialization vector across encryptions in the IDP server. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to launch further attacks on the system.

title: Ruby Recurly Client Python Library Resource.get method server-side request forgery
description: Ruby Recurly Client Ruby Library is vulnerable to server-side request forgery, caused by a flaw in the Resource#find method. By using a specially-crafted argument, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to compromise the API keys or other critical resources.

title: PyAnyAPI YAML parsing function command execution
description: PyAnyAPI could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary commands on the system, caused by an exploitable vulnerability exists in the YAML parsing function in the YAMLParser method in Interfaces.py. By inserting Python into loaded YAML, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary commands on the system.

title: MLAlchemy YAML parsing function command execution
description: MLAlchemy could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary commands on the system, caused by an exploitable vulnerability exists in the YAML parsing function in the parse_yaml_query method in parser.py. By inserting Python into loaded YAML, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary commands on the system.

title: OwlMixin YAML parsing function command execution
description: OwlMixin could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary commands on the system, caused by an exploitable vulnerability exists in the YAML loading function in util.py. By inserting Python into loaded YAML, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary commands on the system.

title: Ladon Framework for Python XXE information disclosure
description: Ladon Framework for Python allow a remote attacker to obtain sensitive information, caused by an XML external entity (XXE) error. By sending specially-crafted SOAP messages, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to obtain sensitive information.

title: Cisco NX-OS Software Python scripting subsystem privilege escalation
description: Cisco NX-OS Software could allow a local authenticated attacker to gain elevated privileges on the system, caused by improper sanitization of user-supplied parameters passed to certain Python functions in the Python scripting subsystem. By using specially-crafted parameters, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to escape the scripting sandbox and execute arbitrary commands with the privileges of the authenticated user.

title: Python Objects/fileobject.c buffer overflow
description: Python is vulnerable to a heap-based buffer overflow, caused by improper bounds checking by the Objects/fileobject.c. By sending an overly large amount of data, a remote attacker could overflow a buffer and possibly execute arbitrary code on the system or cause the application to crash.

title: Gentoo dev-python/flower package privilege escalation
description: Gentoo dev-python/flower package could allow a local authenticated attacker to gain elevated privileges on the system, caused by setting a PID file ownership to a non-root account. By leveraging access to a non-root account for PID file modification, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to kill arbitrary processes on the system.

title: pysaml2 python optimizations security bypass
description: pysaml2 could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by a flaw when python optimizations enabled. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to bypass access restrictions to log in as any user.

title: python-fedora open redirect
description: python-fedora could allow a remote attacker to conduct phishing attacks, caused by an open redirect vulnerability. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability using a specially-crafted URL to redirect a victim to arbitrary Web sites.

title: Multiple Odoo products Database Anonymization module code exec
description: Multiple Odoo products could allow a remote authenticated attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by a flaw in the Database Anonymization module. By sending a specially-crafted malicious anonymization data file, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary Python code.

title: E2OpenPlugins OpenWebif Plugin code execution
description: E2OpenPlugins OpenWebif Plugin could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by a flaw in the saveConfig function of "plugin/controllers/models/config.py. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability using api/saveconfig to execute arbitrary Python code or OS commands on the system.

title: Tablib Databook code execution
description: Tablib could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by a flaw in the Databook loading function. By inserting python into loaded yaml, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Mercurial Python debugger code execution
description: Mercurial could allow a remote authenticated attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by improper validation of the repository name. By using "--debugger" as a repository name, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Oracle MySQL Connectors Connector/Python unspecified
description: An unspecified vulnerability in Oracle MySQL related to the Connectors Connector/Python component could allow an authenticated attacker to cause no confidentiality impact, low integrity impact, and no availability impact.

title: cloudflare-scrape code execution
description: cloudflare-scrape could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system. By persuading a victim to visit a specially crafted Web site, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary Python code on the system.

title: Python code execution
description: Python could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by an invalid search path flaw for python3.dll loading. By persuading a victim to open a specially-crafted file, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Python pgAdmin4 DLL code execution
description: Python could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by the loading of (uuid.dll) and other dynamic-linked libraries in an insecure manner. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability using pgAdmin4 to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: html5lib html5lib-python special characters cross-site scripting
description: html5lib html5lib-python is vulnerable to cross-site scripting, caused by improper validation of user-supplied input. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to inject malicious script into a Web page which would be executed in a victim's Web browser within the security context of the hosting Web site, once the page is viewed. An attacker could use this vulnerability to steal the victim's cookie-based authentication credentials.

title: html5lib html5lib-python <(less than) character cross-site scripting
description: html5lib html5lib-python is vulnerable to cross-site scripting, caused by improper validation of user-supplied input. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to inject malicious script into a Web page which would be executed in a victim's Web browser within the security context of the hosting Web site, once the page is viewed. An attacker could use this vulnerability to steal the victim's cookie-based authentication credentials.

title: Python oslo.middlewar package information disclosure
description: Python oslo.middlewar package could allow a local authenticated attacker to obtain sensitive information, caused by including sensitive data in the CatchError class. A local attacker could exploit this vulnerability to obtain sensitive information.

title: Java and Python server-side request forgery
description: Java and Python are vulnerable to server-side request forgery, caused by an FTP protocol injection flaw in the built-in URL fetching library (urllib2 in Python 2 and urllib in Python 3) and Java's FTP URL handling code. By persuading a user to visit a malicious Web site, a remote attacker could send a malformed HTTP request to read arbitrary files. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to gain access to the system.

title: Java and Python man-in-the-middle
description: Java and Python are vulnerable to a mna-in-the-middle attacks, caused by an FTP protocol injection flaw in the built-in URL fetching library (urllib2 in Python 2 and urllib in Python 3) and Java's FTP URL handling code. By persuading a victim to visit a specially crafted Web site, a remote authenticated attacker could exploit this vulnerability to inject an HTTP redirect to bootstrap this attack.

title: Java and Python XXE injection
description: Java and Python could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by an FTP protocol injection flaw in the built-in URL fetching library (urllib2 in Python 2 and urllib in Python 3) and Java's FTP URL handling code. By persuading a victim to visit a specially crafted Web site, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to inject FTP commands into the protocol stream and identify the victim's internal IP address, determine the appropriate packet alignment and launch further attacks on the system.

title: Python DecodeAdpcmImaQT buffer overflow
description: Python is vulnerable to a buffer overflow, caused by a flaw in the DecodeAdpcmImaQT function in the ctypes module. By persuading a victim to open a specially-crafted file, an attacker could overflow a buffer and execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: python-jose unspecified
description: An unspecified error in python-jose has an unknown impact by leveraging failure to use a constant time comparison for HMAC keys.

title: Plone CMS str.format security bypass
description: Plone CMS could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by a flaw in the str.format function. By leveraging the Python string format method, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to bypass a sandbox protection mechanism and obtain sensitive information.

title: Ubuntu Apport remote code execution
description: Ubuntu Apport could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary python code on the system, caused by an error in apport/ui.py. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary python code on the system.

title: Ubuntu Apport directory traversal
description: Ubuntu Apport could allow a local attacker to traverse directories on the system caused by the errors in the Apport crash file Package and SourcePackage fields. A local attacker could send a specially-crafted request containing "dot dot" sequences (/../) to execute arbitrary Python files from the local system.

title: Python cryptography HKDF security bypass
description: Python cryptography could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions. HKDF returns an empty byte-string if used with a length less than algorithm.digest_size. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to bypass security restrictions and perform unauthorized actions.

title: Python urllib3 library security bypass
description: Python could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by the improper validation of TLS certificates by the PyOpenSSL contrib module in the urllib3 library. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to perform man-in-the-middle and information leakage attacks.

title: Oracle MySQL Connector Connector/Python unspecified
description: An unspecified vulnerability in Oracle MySQL Connector related to the Connector/Python component has low confidentiality impact, low integrity impact, and low availability impact.

title: Trend Micro Virtual Mobile Infrastructure apns_worker.py command execution
description: Trend Micro Virtual Mobile Infrastructure could allow a remote authenticated attacker to execute arbitrary commands on the system, caused by an error in the apns_worker.py python script. By injecting system commands into the password field, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary commands on the system with root privileges.

title: Python HPACK library for HTTP/2 denial of service
description: Python HPACK library for HTTP/2 is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by an error in the HTTP/2 implementation. By inserting a header field that is exactly the size of the HPACK dynamic header table into the dynamic header table, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause an HPACK Bomb attack.

title: Python Priority library for HTTP/2 denial of service
description: Python Priority library for HTTP/2 is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by allocating unbounded amounts of memory for every possible HTTP/2 stream ID. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to consume all available CPU resources.

title: Python HTTP_PROXY environment variable HTTP traffic redirect
description:
Python could allow a remote attacker to redirect HTTP traffic of CGI application, caused by the failure to protect applications from the presence of untrusted client data in the HTTP_PROXY environment variable. By using a specially-crafted Proxy header in a HTTP request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to redirect outbound HTTP traffic to arbitrary proxy server.

This is also known as the "HTTPOXY" vulnerability.

title: Python HTTP_PROXY environment variable HTTP traffic redirect
description:
Python could allow a remote attacker to redirect HTTP traffic of CGI application, caused by the failure to protect applications from the presence of untrusted client data in the HTTP_PROXY environment variable. By using a specially-crafted Proxy header in a HTTP request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to redirect outbound HTTP traffic to arbitrary proxy server.

This is also known as the "HTTPOXY" vulnerability.

title: Python python-3.5.2.exe DLL code execution
description: Python could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by the loading of (fwbase.dll) dynamic-linked libraries by executable installers. By placing a DLL in the users "Downloads" directory, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: The python-docx package XXE denial of service
description: The python-docx package is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by an XML External Entity Injection (XXE) error when processing XML data. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to expose sensitive information or consume all available memory resources.

title: Python's smtplib library stripping attack
description: Python's smtplib library is vulnerable to a stripping attack. An exception isn't returned by the Python's smtplib library if StartTLS fails to establish correctly in the SMTP.starttls() function. An attacker with man-in-the-middle ability could exploit this vulnerability to strip out the STARTTLS command without generating an exception on the python SMTP client application and prevent the establishment of the TLS layer.

title: urllib2 and urllib for Python header injection
description: urllib2 and urllib for Python are vulnerable to HTTP header injection, caused by improper validation of input. By persuading a victim to visit a specially-crafted Web page, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to inject arbitrary HTTP headers, which will allow the attacker to conduct various attacks against the vulnerable system, including cross-site scripting, cache poisoning or session hijacking.

title: zipimport module for Python zipimport.c buffer overflow
description: zipimport module for Python is vulnerable to a heap-based buffer overflow, caused by improper bounds checking by the get_data() function in zipimport.c. A remote attacker could overflow a buffer and execute arbitrary code on the system or cause the application to crash.

title: Apache Qpid Proton python API information disclosure
description: Apache Qpid could allow a remote attacker to obtain sensitive information, caused by the use of the Proton python API to provision an SSL/TLS encrypted TCP connection by messaging applications. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability using man-in-the-middle techniques to obtain messages being sent in clear text.

title: Python DLL code execution
description: Python could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by the loading of dynamic-linked libraries by executable installers. By placing a DLL in the users "Downloads" directory, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Python (Python-RSA) verify function spoofing
description: Python (Python-RSA) could allow a remote attacker to conduct spoofing attacks, an error in the verify function. By using a malformed signature, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to spoof signatures.

title: IBM SPSS Statistics privilege escalation
description: IBM SPSS Statistics uses python scripts that have write permissions to Everyone. A local user can add malicious OS commands to the python code. These command will later be executed in case another user (for example an administrator) opens SPSS and uses that module.

title: Python xmlrpc library denial of service
description: Python is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by the failure to restrict the size of a gzip compressed HTTP responses by the xmlrpc library. By connecting to a malicious server, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to consume an overly large amount of memory resources.

title: Users Ultra Plugin for WordPress xoo.userultra.user.php file upload
description: Users Ultra Plugin for WordPress could allow a remote attacker to upload arbitrary files, caused by the improper validation of MIME files or file size by the xoo.userultra.user.php script.. By sending a specially-crafted HTTP POST request, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to upload a malicious csv file, which could allow the attacker to execute arbitrary python code on the vulnerable system.
platform: WordPress Users Ultra Plugin for WordPress 1.5.50

title: AlienVault Unified Security Management cPickle objects code execution
description: AlienVault Unified Security Management could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by the deserialization of cPickle objects within the av-forward Python daemon. By sending specially crafted data, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system with avforw account.

title: Python pack_string buffer overflow
description: Python is vulnerable to a heap-based buffer overflow, caused by improper bounds checking by the pack_string function. By sending an overly long string argument to the Profile.addinfo method, a remote attacker could overflow a buffer and execute arbitrary code on the system or cause the application to crash.

title: Python array.fromstring() code execution
description: Python could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by a  use-after-free in the array.fromstring() function. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability using the fromstring() call to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Python strop.replace() integer overflow
description: Python could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by an integer overflow in the strop.replace() function. By sending an overly long string, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Python product_setstate() code execution
description: Python could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by an out-of-bounds read in the product_setstate() function. By invoking the function, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to obtain sensitive information, execute arbitrary code on the system or cause the application to crash.

title: Python xmlparse_setattro() code execution
description: Python could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by a type confusion error in the xmlparse_setattro() function. By invoking the function, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Python time_strftime() information disclosure
description: Python could allow a remote attacker to obtain sensitive information, caused by a buffer over-read error in the time_strftime() function. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to view the contents of adjacent memory.

title: Python scan_eol() information disclosure
description: Python could allow a remote attacker to obtain sensitive information, caused by a buffer over-read error in the scan_eol() function. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to view the contents of adjacent memory.

title: Ubuntu Apport Python module imports privilege escalation
description: Ubuntu Apport could allow a local attacker to gain elevated privileges on the system, caused by improper handling of Python module imports. By sending a specially-crafted request, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to gain elevated privileges and run programs as an administrator.

title: OpenStack Swift-on-File (Swiftonfile) code execution
description: OpenStack Swift-on-File could allow a remote authenticated attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by the failure to properly restrict use of the pickle Python module when loading metadata. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Linux Kernel Python security bypass
description: Linux Kernel could allow a local attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused  by the failure to prevent the running of executables. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability using the python script to run the executable file.

title: OpenStack Ironic Inspector Flask console code execution
description: OpenStack Ironic Inspector could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by an error when debug mode is enabled. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to gain access to the Flask console and execute arbitrary Python code on the system.

title: Juniper Junos command shell privilege escalation
description: Juniper Junos could allow a local authenticated attacker to gain elevated privileges on the system, caused by python flaws in the command shell. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary python code on the system.

title: Python for Windows code execution
description: Python for Windows could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by the insecure loading of the readline.pyd DLL. By persuading a victim to open a specially crafted file, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: Palo Alto Networks Panorama VM Appliance code execution
description: Palo Alto Networks Panorama VM Appliance could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary  code on the system, caused by a flaw related to the processing of new firmware. By using a specially-crafted firmware, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary Python code on the system.

title: Python tlslite library denial of service
description: Python is vulnerable to a denial of service, caused by a flaw in the tlslite library. By using a specially-crafted message, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause the process to crash.

title: Python IDLE denial of service
description: Python IDLE is vulnerable to a denial of service. By sending an overly long string argument, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to cause the application to crash.

title: Python pip mirroring support security bypass
description: Python pip could allow a remote attacker to bypass security restrictions, caused by the implementation of the mirroring support without authentication checks. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to download software over insecure links.

title: Cisco Nexus devices privilege escalation
description: Cisco Nexus devices could allow a local authenticated attacker to gain elevated privileges on the system, caused by insufficient hardening of the operating system. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary Python scripts and gain root privileges on the system.

title: Cisco Nexus 7000 privilege escalation
description: Cisco Nexus 7000 could allow a local authenticated attacker to gain elevated privileges on the system, caused by incomplete privilege separation of the Python scripting engine across multiple VDCs. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to remove files owned by a separate VDC.

title: IBM PowerVC KVM host privilege escalation
description: An attacker local to a KVM host managed by PowerVC 1.2.2.1 or 1.2.2.2 may obtain a python prompt running as the nova service user via an unauthenticated local port. This connection may be used to glean PowerVC service user credentials. These can in turn be used to perform PowerVC operations restricted to admin users, and/or to obtain the credentials PowerVC uses to manage other hosts, storage, etc., including root credentials.

title: python-kerberos checkPassword() spoofing
description: python-kerberos could allow a remote attacker to conduct spoofing attacks, caused by the failure to verify KDC authenticity by the checkPassword() function. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability using man-in-the-middle techniques to spoof a KDC.

title: python-tornado XSRF cookie BREACH
description: python-tornado is vulnerable to BREACH attack, caused by an error in the XSRF cookie. By sending a series of specially-crafted requests, a remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability to allow a side-channel attack against TLS. This vulnerability was demonstrated at BlackHat 2013 and a corresponding tool released known as "BREACH".

title: Python ssl.match_hostname() function spoofing
description: Python could allow a remote attacker to conduct spoofing attacks, caused by an error when handling certificates that contain hostnames with wildcard by the ssl.match_hostname() function. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability using man-in-the-middle techniques to spoof SSL servers, which could be used to launch further attacks against the victim.

title: python-dbusmock ddTemplate() D-Bus method and  DBusTestCase.spawn_server_template() method code execution
description: python-dbusmock could allow a remote attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by a flaw in the AddTemplate() D-Bus method and  DBusTestCase.spawn_server_template() method. By persuading a victim to open a specially-crafted .pyc file, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary code on the system.

title: OpenStack keystonemiddleware and python-keystoneclient s3_token middleware man-in-the-middle
description: OpenStack keystonemiddleware and python-keystoneclient is vulnerable to a man-in-the-middle attack, caused by an error in the api-paste.ini configuration file. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability using a specially-crafted handshake to conduct man-in-the-middle attacks to decrypt and modify traffic.

title: Cisco Web Security Appliance status checking code execution
description: Cisco Web Security Appliance could allow a local attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by the improper usage and handling of the pickle Python module by the status checking process of support remote access tunnels. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary Python code on the system.

title: Cisco Web Security Appliance status-checking privilege escalation
description: Cisco Web Security Appliance could allow a local authenticated attacker to gain elevated privileges on the system, caused by the improper usage and handling of the pickle Python module by the status-checking process. By sending a specially-crafted pickle file, an attacker could exploit this vulnerability to execute arbitrary Python code on the system.

title: Python Restkit SSL/TLS certificates spoofing
description: Python Restkit could allow a remote attacker to conduct spoofing attacks, caused by the improper validation of SSL/TLS certificates. An attacker could exploit this vulnerability to spoof TLS servers.
